  "description": [
    "Friday 10 May 1963 Area Estates Offer Sailors Tour Discounts The Newport Preservation So ciety has announced special prices to members of the Armed Forces who wish to tour the historical homes and mansions of Newport The special price includes indi vidual tours of a group of his torical homes and two mansions Two of the most famous mansions in the East The Breakers and The Elms are included in this group In addition to the two man sions the group ticket includes admission to the NieholasWan tonHunter House the Wanton LymanHazard House ami White hall The total individual admis sion price is 550 But Service men and women may tour all six for a special price of 350 Members of the Armed Forces may also take advantage of in dividual special price admissions to either The Breakers or The Elms The special fee for admis sion t the former is 1 25 and sloo to the latter The two mansions are located in the Bellevue section of New port The Elins located on Bel levue Avenue was designed by the noted Philadelphia architect Horace Trumbauer who took for his inspiration the beautiful Cha teau dAsnieres in France The Breakers"
